## Documentation Gap

**Package:** `Azure.ResourceManager.Playwright`
**Service directory:** `sdk/playwright/Azure.ResourceManager.Playwright/`
**Triggered by:** PR #57806 by @azure-sdk

## What Changed

Version `1.1.0-beta.1` was released (2026-04-06) with an upgrade to API version `2026-02-01-preview`, introducing:
- `Identity` property (`ManagedServiceIdentity`) on `PlaywrightWorkspaceData` and `PlaywrightWorkspacePatch`
- `Reporting` property (`PlaywrightEnablementStatus?`) on `PlaywrightWorkspaceProperties` and `PlaywrightWorkspaceUpdateProperties`
- `StorageUri` property (`Uri`) on `PlaywrightWorkspaceProperties` and `PlaywrightWorkspaceUpdateProperties`

## Gaps Found

- The `Examples` section of the README contains only a generic link to [Azure SDK .NET management samples](https://aka.ms/azuresdk-net-mgmt-samples) — no service-specific code snippets exist
- There are no snippet-backed sample test files under `tests/Samples/` (the directory does not exist)
- The new `Identity` (Managed Service Identity), `Reporting`, and `StorageUri` properties introduced in `1.1.0-beta.1` are documented only in the CHANGELOG, not reflected in any README example or code sample
- The `Key concepts` section is a stub pointing to generic SDK documentation with no Playwright-specific content describing workspaces, quota, or other service concepts

<details>
<summary><strong>📐 Implementation Guide</strong></summary>

This section contains step-by-step instructions for a coding agent to implement the changes described above.

### Step 1: Modify files

**File:** `sdk/playwright/Azure.ResourceManager.Playwright/README.md`  
**Action:** Edit — expand the `Key concepts` and `Examples` sections

In `## Key concepts`, replace the current single-link paragraph with a brief description of the key resource types:

```markdown
## Key concepts

The `Azure.ResourceManager.Playwright` library manages the following resource types:

- **PlaywrightWorkspace** (`PlaywrightWorkspaceResource`) — the top-level resource representing a Microsoft Playwright Testing workspace. It exposes CRUD operations and contains properties such as `Identity` (for Managed Service Identity), `Reporting` (to enable/disable built-in reporting), and `StorageUri` (the URI of an associated storage account).

Key concepts of the Azure Resource Manager SDK for .NET can be found [here](https://azure.github.io/azure-sdk/dotnet_introduction.html).
```

In `## Examples`, replace the current single-link paragraph with a snippet placeholder (the tooling will inject actual code after the snippet test file is created):

```markdown
## Examples

### Create a Playwright Workspace

```C# Snippet:Sample_PlaywrightWorkspace_CreateOrUpdate
```

### Create a Playwright Workspace with Managed Identity

```C# Snippet:Sample_PlaywrightWorkspace_CreateWithManagedIdentity
```

### Enable Reporting on a Playwright Workspace

```C# Snippet:Sample_PlaywrightWorkspace_EnableReporting
```

For more code samples, see the [.NET Management Library Code Samples](https://aka.ms/azuresdk-net-mgmt-samples).
```

### Step 2: Add or update code snippets

Create a new test sample file at:  
**`sdk/playwright/Azure.ResourceManager.Playwright/tests/Samples/Sample1_PlaywrightWorkspace.cs`**

```csharp
// Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation. All rights reserved.
// Licensed under the MIT License.

using System;
using System.Threading.Tasks;
using Azure.Core;
using Azure.Core.TestFramework;
using Azure.Identity;
using Azure.ResourceManager;
using Azure.ResourceManager.Models;
using Azure.ResourceManager.Playwright.Models;
using Azure.ResourceManager.Resources;
using NUnit.Framework;

namespace Azure.ResourceManager.Playwright.Tests.Samples
{
    public class Sample1_PlaywrightWorkspace : SamplesBase<PlaywrightManagementTestEnvironment>
    {
        [Test]
        [SyncOnly]
        [Ignore("Only verifying that the sample builds")]
        public async Task CreateOrUpdateWorkspace()
        {
            #region Snippet:Sample_PlaywrightWorkspace_CreateOrUpdate
            ArmClient client = new ArmClient(new DefaultAzureCredential());

            SubscriptionResource subscription = await client.GetDefaultSubscriptionAsync();
            ResourceGroupResource resourceGroup = await subscription
                .GetResourceGroupAsync("myResourceGroup");

            PlaywrightWorkspaceCollection workspaces = resourceGroup.GetPlaywrightWorkspaces();

            string workspaceName = "myPlaywrightWorkspace";
            AzureLocation location = AzureLocation.EastUS;

            PlaywrightWorkspaceData data = new PlaywrightWorkspaceData(location);

            ArmOperation<PlaywrightWorkspaceResource> operation = await workspaces
                .CreateOrUpdateAsync(WaitUntil.Completed, workspaceName, data);

            PlaywrightWorkspaceResource workspace = operation.Value;
            Console.WriteLine($"Created workspace: {workspace.Data.Name}");
            #endregion
        }

        [Test]
        [SyncOnly]
        [Ignore("Only verifying that the sample builds")]
        public async Task CreateWorkspaceWithManagedIdentity()
        {
            #region Snippet:Sample_PlaywrightWorkspace_CreateWithManagedIdentity
            ArmClient client = new ArmClient(new DefaultAzureCredential());

            SubscriptionResource subscription = await client.GetDefaultSubscriptionAsync();
            ResourceGroupResource resourceGroup = await subscription
                .GetResourceGroupAsync("myResourceGroup");

            PlaywrightWorkspaceCollection workspaces = resourceGroup.GetPlaywrightWorkspaces();

            string workspaceName = "myPlaywrightWorkspace";
            AzureLocation location = AzureLocation.EastUS;

            PlaywrightWorkspaceData data = new PlaywrightWorkspaceData(location)
            {
                Identity = new ManagedServiceIdentity(ManagedServiceIdentityType.SystemAssigned)
            };

            ArmOperation<PlaywrightWorkspaceResource> operation = await workspaces
                .CreateOrUpdateAsync(WaitUntil.Completed, workspaceName, data);

            PlaywrightWorkspaceResource workspace = operation.Value;
            Console.WriteLine($"Workspace principal ID: {workspace.Data.Identity?.PrincipalId}");
            #endregion
        }

        [Test]
        [SyncOnly]
        [Ignore("Only verifying that the sample builds")]
        public async Task EnableReporting()
        {
            #region Snippet:Sample_PlaywrightWorkspace_EnableReporting
            ArmClient client = new ArmClient(new DefaultAzureCredential());

            SubscriptionResource subscription = await client.GetDefaultSubscriptionAsync();
            ResourceGroupResource resourceGroup = await subscription
                .GetResourceGroupAsync("myResourceGroup");

            PlaywrightWorkspaceResource workspace = await resourceGroup
                .GetPlaywrightWorkspaceAsync("myPlaywrightWorkspace");

            PlaywrightWorkspacePatch patch = new PlaywrightWorkspacePatch
            {
                Properties = new PlaywrightWorkspaceUpdateProperties
                {
                    Reporting = PlaywrightEnablementStatus.Enabled
                }
            };

            PlaywrightWorkspaceResource updated = await workspace.UpdateAsync(patch);
            Console.WriteLine($"Reporting status: {updated.Data.Properties?.Reporting}");
            #endregion
        }
    }
}
```

The snippet names used above must match exactly between the test file `#region` tags and the README placeholder fences:
- `Sample_PlaywrightWorkspace_CreateOrUpdate`
- `Sample_PlaywrightWorkspace_CreateWithManagedIdentity`
- `Sample_PlaywrightWorkspace_EnableReporting`

Refer to `sdk/keyvault/Azure.Security.KeyVault.Secrets/tests/samples/Sample1_HelloWorld.cs` as a canonical example.

